<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1398,684,746]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Many museum specimens were identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Oberthur, 1881" authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1881" box="[702,905,685,711]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constantinaria">
<emphasis box="[702,905,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">C. constantinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but will often actually belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brehm" authorityYear="2018" box="[1280,1398,684,711]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occulta" status="stat. rev.">
<emphasis box="[1280,1398,684,711]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">C. occulta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,288,720,746]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">stat. rev.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and other species. The female is unknown.
</paragraph>
